<TITLE> China firework factory blast kills four </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 BEIJING, Aug 28 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - An explosion at a firework factory in northern China killed four people and seriously injured another two, the official Xinhua agency reported. Surviving workers said they saw one of the injured light a fire on Tuesday to repair equipment in a part of the complex where naked flames were forbidden, the report said. Police have detained one person and are hunting for two other shareholders in the privately-owned factory. Explosions at a firecracker company killed 36 in 2006. Hundreds of fireworks accidents cause around 450 deaths in China each year. Xinhua reported earlier this year that around 30 percent of firecrackers sold nationwide were substanda
